commit.message:
Add Data.Map.Ordered.Strict

To facilitate code reuse between `Data.Map.Ordered` and
`Data.Map.Ordered.Strict`, I migrated the existing `Data.Map.Ordered`
module to `Data.Map.Ordered.Internal`.

Fixes #10.

Define "pass-through" instances for Bias

`OMap` and `OSet` define several instances that `Bias` lacks, which
makes it somewhat awkward to productively use `Bias` without
excessive amounts of newtype wrapping and unwrapping. This patch
derives these instances for `Bias` to make this easier.
bump version to 0.2.1

commit.message:
Fix the build on old GHCs

Fixes #11. Fixes #12.
bump version to 0.2

more instances

Two Monoid instances each for OSet and OMap, and a Traversable instance
for OMap. We used to avoid these because they had worse asymptotics than
in Set and Map, but that's no barrier any more.

Fixes issue #3.

admit that not everything can be done super fast

Some operations are both useful and can't be done as fast in the ordered
setting as when you don't need to remember the ordering. Okay. Let's
admit that, and include information about just how much slower it is in
the documentation.

Replaces pull request #7.
minor tweaks
whitespace only
five years is a long enough support window
derived Functor instance for OMap
